INTENT_LIST 

IntentId:  

intentName: RequestSoftware 

description: Request a software license. 

Example: I need Microsoft Word software. 

Slots: 

- slotID: Microsoft 

slotName: microsoftSoftware 

type: string  

possibleValues: [Word, Excel, PowerPoint] 

description: Microsoft software 

-slotID: Adobe 

slotName: adobeSoftware 

type: string 

description: Adobe Software 

possibleValues: [Photoshop, Ilustrator, InDesign] 

intentId: OrderSupplies 

intentName: Order Supplies  

description: Order supplies 

Example: I need to order red pens. 

Slots: 

- slotID: SupplyColors 

slotName: supplyColors 

type: string 

description: Office supply color options 

Possible values: [Red, Blue, Black, Pink, Yellow, White, Green,] 

- slotID: SupplyType 

slotName: supplyType 

type: string 

description: Supply item type.  

possibleValues: [pen, paper, ink] 

-slotID: SupplyAmount 

slotName: supplyAmount 

Type: integer 

Description: Amount of the supply item that needs to be ordered.  

INSTRUCTION 

Above is a INTENT_LIST of possible user intents. These intents are categorized into slots. These slots have may have corresponding descriptions, examples, and values. For example, PossibleValues gives a list of the only values a slot can take. If the user utterance contains slots or intents that cannot be categorized with the provided INTENT_LIST,  provide the value of "null" instead. If the user utterance contains intents or slots with any "null" value, respond with "UNABLE TO COMPLETE REQUEST"
Use the INTENT_LIST to determine intent of the of the user UTTERANCE.  Give your response in JSON.
